    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Remove all contents from the list, so it is once again empty. Client is responsible for reclaiming storage used by the list elements.

      • insert

        void insert(E item)
        Insert an element at the current location. The client must ensure that the list’s capacity is not exceeded.
        Parameters:
        item - The element to be inserted.

      • append

        void append(E item)
        Append an element at the end of the list. The client must ensure that the list’s capacity is not exceeded.
        Parameters:
        item - The element to be appended.

      • remove

        void prev()
        Move the current position one step left. No change if already at beginning.

      • next

        void next()
        Move the current position one step right. No change if already at end.
